Package: breedtools
Title: Tools for Multi-Environment Breedbase Phenotype Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Authors@R: 
    person("Cristiano", "Simoes", email = "ccsimoes263@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Cristiano Simoes [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Cristiano Simoes <ccsimoes263@gmail.com>
Description: Loads Breedbase-style phenotype data from Excel or CSV files,
    prepares it for multi-environment analysis, checks environment variance
    compatibility with Hartley's Fmax test, and groups environments with
    Lin-style genotype-by-environment interaction tests.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 8.0.0
Imports:
    dplyr,
    tidyr,
    purrr,
    readxl,
    leaflet,
    htmltools,
    tibble,
    tools,
    graphics,
    grDevices,
    jsonlite,
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
